# Aries-Edge Schemas

Shared schema definitions for the Aries-Edge Platform. This package provides consistent data models across all services.

## Installation

```bash
npm install @aries-edge/schemas
```

## Usage

### TypeScript/JavaScript

```typescript
import { UserSchema, CameraSchema, DetectionSchema } from '@aries-edge/schemas';

// Validate user data
const userData = {
  username: 'john_doe',
  email: 'john@example.com',
  full_name: 'John Doe',
  role: 'operator',
  status: 'active'
};

const validatedUser = UserSchema.parse(userData);
```

### Python

```python
from aries_edge_schemas import User, CreateUser, Camera

# Create a new user
new_user = CreateUser(
    username="john_doe",
    email="john@example.com", 
    full_name="John Doe",
    role="operator",
    password="secure_password123"
)

# Validate camera data
camera = Camera(
    id="123e4567-e89b-12d3-a456-426614174000",
    name="Front Door Camera",
    type="ip",
    url="rtsp://192.168.1.100:554/stream",
    status="online",
    is_active=True
)
```

## Schema Types

### User Management
- `UserSchema` - Complete user model
- `CreateUserSchema` - User creation
- `UpdateUserSchema` - User updates
- `LoginSchema` - Authentication
- `TokenSchema` - JWT tokens
- `ApiKeySchema` - API key management

### Camera & Streaming
- `CameraSchema` - Camera configuration
- `StreamSchema` - Stream settings
- `CreateCameraSchema` - Camera creation
- `CreateStreamSchema` - Stream creation

### Analytics & Detection
- `DetectionSchema` - Object detection results
- `AnalyticsEventSchema` - Analytics events
- `BoundingBoxSchema` - Object bounding boxes
- `DetectionClassSchema` - COCO detection classes

### WebSocket Messages
- `WsMessageSchema` - Base WebSocket message
- `DetectionWsMessageSchema` - Detection messages
- `AnalyticsWsMessageSchema` - Analytics messages

### Configuration
- `SystemConfigSchema` - System settings
- `UpdateSystemConfigSchema` - Configuration updates

## Validation

All schemas include comprehensive validation:

- UUID format validation
- Email format validation
- URL format validation  
- Enum value validation
- Numeric range validation
- String length validation
- Date/time format validation

## Cross-Language Compatibility

The schemas are designed to be compatible between TypeScript and Python implementations, ensuring consistent data validation across the entire stack.
